from pyspark.sql.functions import trim, col, to_timestamp, when, round
import re

df = spark.table("project.default.supply_chain_dataset")

# 1. Normalize column names
def clean_col(name):
    n = re.sub(r"[^0-9A-Za-z]+", "_", name).strip("_").lower()
    n = re.sub(r"_+", "_", n)
    return n

df = df.toDF(*[clean_col(c) for c in df.columns])

# Drop columns
df = df.drop("order_customer_id","order_item_cardprod_id", "order_item_discount", "order_item_discount_rate", "order_item_id", "order_item_product_price", "order_item_quantity", "order_item_total", "order_zipcode", "product_image", "product_description")
display(df)

# 2. Identify date columns
order_date_candidates = [c for c in df.columns if "order" in c and "date" in c]
shipping_date_candidates = [c for c in df.columns if "shipping" in c and "date" in c]

order_col = order_date_candidates[0] if order_date_candidates else None
ship_col  = shipping_date_candidates[0] if shipping_date_candidates else None

# 3. Parse dates
if order_col:
    df = df.withColumn("order_date_ts", to_timestamp(col(order_col), "M/d/yyyy H:mm"))
if ship_col:
    df = df.withColumn("shipping_date_ts", to_timestamp(col(ship_col), "M/d/yyyy H:mm"))

# 4. Derived metrics
if "days_for_shipping_real" in df.columns and "days_for_shipment_scheduled" in df.columns:
    df = df.withColumn(
        "shipping_delay_days",
        col("days_for_shipping_real").cast("double") - col("days_for_shipment_scheduled").cast("double"))

    threshold = 0.0
    df = df.withColumn(
        "is_late_delivery",
        when(col("shipping_delay_days").isNull(), None)
        .when(col("shipping_delay_days") > threshold, 1)
        .otherwise(0))

display(df)

      SELECT 
        YEAR(try_to_timestamp(order_date_dateorders, 'M/d/yyyy H:mm')) AS order_year,
        MONTH(try_to_timestamp(order_date_dateorders, 'M/d/yyyy H:mm')) AS order_month,
        COUNT(*) AS total_orders
      FROM project.default.supply_chain_cleaned
      WHERE try_to_timestamp(order_date_dateorders, 'M/d/yyyy H:mm') IS NOT NULL
        AND YEAR(try_to_timestamp(order_date_dateorders, 'M/d/yyyy H:mm')) < 2018
      GROUP BY 
        YEAR(try_to_timestamp(order_date_dateorders, 'M/d/yyyy H:mm')), 
        MONTH(try_to_timestamp(order_date_dateorders, 'M/d/yyyy H:mm'))
      ORDER BY order_year, order_month

      SELECT 
          category_name,
          COUNT(*) AS total_orders,
          SUM(
              CASE 
                  WHEN delivery_status = 'Late' OR late_delivery_risk = 1 THEN 1
                  ELSE 0
              END) AS late_orders, ROUND(100.0 * SUM(
                  CASE 
                      WHEN delivery_status = 'Late' OR late_delivery_risk = 1 THEN 1
                      ELSE 0
                  END) / COUNT(*), 2) AS late_rate
      FROM project.default.supply_chain_cleaned
      GROUP BY category_name
      ORDER BY late_rate DESC;

      CREATE OR REPLACE VIEW project.default.city_shipping AS
      WITH supply_chain_enriched AS (
        SELECT
          customer_city,
          latitude,
          longitude,
          days_for_shipping_real,
          days_for_shipment_scheduled,
          CASE 
            WHEN days_for_shipping_real > days_for_shipment_scheduled THEN 1
            ELSE 0
          END AS is_late_delivery
        FROM project.default.supply_chain_cleaned
        WHERE latitude IS NOT NULL AND longitude IS NOT NULL
      )
      SELECT
        customer_city,
        latitude,
        longitude,
        COUNT(*) AS total_orders,
        SUM(is_late_delivery) AS late_count,
        ROUND(100.0 * SUM(is_late_delivery) / COUNT(*), 2) AS late_rate_pct,
        ROUND(AVG(days_for_shipping_real - days_for_shipment_scheduled), 2) AS avg_delay_days
      FROM supply_chain_enriched
      GROUP BY customer_city, latitude, longitude
      ORDER BY late_rate_pct DESC;
      SELECT * FROM project.default.city_shipping;
